content.description: Stairway to Heaven 5.4 ORANGE Start about 5 feet from the left end of the wall. Climb easy stairs until reaching the steep part of the wall.  Use the two finger tip holds in the horizontal crack.  Move right to the vertical crack to finish.
content.protection: Top anchor from trees and/or larger gear. Watch for sharp edges.
content.location: On the little Pinnacle.  Five feet right of the left end of the wall.

content.description: Slow and Mellow 5.5 YELLOW About mid way in the left wall the lower face becomes more steep and begins to overhang. Start on the left side of the steep section.  Move up easy foot and hand holds aiming for the peak of the pinnacle.
content.protection: Top anchor from trees and/or large gear. Watch for sharp edges at the top.
content.location: The left side of the steep section of the left wall of the Little Pinnacle

content.description: Hold the Line 5.6. RED Start on the far left of the wall just right of the dirty crack.  Climb the face following the direct line to the top.  The left hand can work the right edge of the crack.
content.protection: Top anchor from trees, some cracks for larger cams or hexes closer to the top. Watch for sharp edges.
content.location: Start on the far left of the wall just right of the dirty crack.

content.description:
The little Pinnacle is almost the 5th Arete but it is a detached free standing pinnacle, but not by much. It has some interesting, fun, easy and moderate routes.              

The Little Pinnacle Right Side
